<p>
  <span class="nym">Naomi</span>
  <span class="gen">f.</span>
  
  <span class="etym"><span class="lang">Hebrew</span> <i>נָעֳמִי</i> 'my pleasantness'.
  </span>
  
</p>
  
<div class="usg">
  <p>The name of an Old Testament character. Wycliffite Bible (1395): <i>Noemy</i>.</p>
</div>
  
  
<div class="def">
  <p>The name came into use among Protestants in the 16th C.</p>
  
  


<dl>
<dt><span class="area">France</span></dt>
<dd>
<dl>
<dt><span class="lang">Middle French</span></dt>
<dd><span class="dim">●</span> <span class="date">1564</span> <span class="name">Noémy</span> <a href="../cite/Noémy/1564/RegPCC-1"><span class="bib_key">RegPCC-1</span> <span class="bib_loc">p. 62</span></a>;
 <span class="date">1568</span> <span class="name">Noémye</span> <a href="../cite/Noémye/1568/RegPCC-1"><span class="bib_key">ibid.</span> <span class="bib_loc">p. 395</span></a>;
 <span class="date">1571</span> <span class="name">Noémi</span> <a href="../cite/Noémi/1571/RegPCC-1"><span class="bib_key">ibid.</span> <span class="bib_loc">p. 465</span></a></dd>
</dl>
</dd>
</dl>


